benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account audit logs with history by account id

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: Successful retrieval for valid accountId (TC01).
GET Method - Empty Response: Empty array when no audit logs (TC02).
GET Method - Authorization: 401 for missing/expired tokens (TC05, TC06).
GET Method - Error Handling & Validation: 400 for invalid accountId (TC04), 404 for non-existent account (TC03), 500 for system error (TC07).
GET Method - Query Parameters: Unsupported parameters are ignored (TC08).
Security: SQL injection test ensures no exposure (TC10).
Performance: Large audit history returns all logs; 100 concurrent requests (TC09, TC11).
Edge Cases: Leading/trailing whitespace, uppercase, max-length UUID, and partial IDs (TC14-TC17).
Regression: AuditLog fields coverage per latest schema (TC12).
gaps: Pagination: No pagination tests for large datasets.
Authorization: No 403 Forbidden scenarios to verify permission-based access.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate-limiting/throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
recommendations: Add pagination tests to ensure proper handling of large datasets (page/size).
Add 403 Forbidden test scenarios to verify permission-based access control.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure bursts stay within SLA.
Add tests for caching behavior including ETag and Cache-Control headers, and cache invalidation.
